					<p class="blurb">The opening of a canal in 1848 led to the birth of modern financial derivatives, and the early demise of some of the men who traded them<br>Written by <strong><a href='https://www.damninteresting.com/contributors/michael-durbin/'>Michael Durbin</a></strong> &bull; 13 minute read</p>
			
